rides.FunFact: All the character voices in the attraction were performed by the original stars of the hit movie, Despicable Me.
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Despicable Me Minion Mayhem™ on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription: Join Gru, his daughters and the mischievous Minions on an unpredictable ride. In Gru's latest scheme, you'll become an actual Minion. It's heartwarming and humorous family fun for everyone.

rides.FunFact:
First ever combination of moving, motion-based ride vehicles, 3-D film and live action.  

This simulator ride's set encompasses 1.5 acres including a virtual 400 foot freefall experience
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out The Amazing Adventures of Spider-Man® on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription: Strap on your 3-D glasses and join the world's most famous web slinger in a high-flying virtual reality ride. You'll soar above the streets, scale skyscrapers and battle bad guys left and right.

rides.FunFact: Some of the characters you can ride include elephant birds from Horton Hatches the Egg; twin camels from One Fish, Two Fish, Red Fish, Blue Fish; cowfish from McElligot's Pool; Mulligatawnies from If I Ran the Zoo; aqua mop tops, dog-a-lopes and more.
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Caro-Seuss-el™ on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription: You'll find some unusual creatures from the imagination of Dr. Seuss on this one-of-a-kind carousel. Make your mount's eyes blink, ears wiggle, or head turn!

rides.FunFact: Dr. Seuss never drew straight lines in his illustrations. Everything was curved, slanted or "wonky." Thus, there are no straight lines in Seuss Landing.
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out The Cat in the Hat™ on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription: Ride your couch through the pages of Dr. Seuss's best-loved children's book. This delightful ride re-creates the story scene for scene.

rides.FunFact:
The initial launch at the beginning of the ride uses more thrust than a 747 jet engine and accelerates faster than the space shuttle. 

Doctor Doom's Fearfall has two towers that each stand 200 feet tall.
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Doctor Doom's Fearfall® on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription: Doctor Doom has strapped you in. Now he's going to rocket you skyward 185 feet into the air, then hurl you back down faster than the force of gravity itself!

rides.FunFact: This is the first flume ride to send riders plummeting below the water level.
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Dudley Do-Right's Ripsaw Falls® on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription: Will you stay dry during the incredibly steep plummet down Ripsaw Falls? Hop in your log for the watery conclusion of this hilarious flume ride to find out!

rides.FunFact: Based on one of the most popular movies ever made, E.T. Adventure™ is one of Universal Studios Florida's most iconic attractions, delighting millions of visitors over the years.
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out E.T. Adventure™ on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription: E.T.'s home planet is dying and he needs your help to save it. Board your flying bike with E.T. and take off on a thrilling (but gentle) ride through the sky.

rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Flight of the Hippogriff™ on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription: Follow Hagrid's instructions as you take off on a family-friendly coaster that spirals and dives around the pumpkin patch, and swoops past Hagrid's hut.

rides.FunFact:
Best New Attraction - 2010, ThemeParkInsider.com

Best Dark Ride - 2011, Amusement Today Golden Ticket Award
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Harry Potter and the Forbidden Journey™ on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblDisplayName: Harry Potter and the Forbidden Journey™
rides.MblShortDescription: Make your way through Hogwarts™ castle. Then join Harry Potter™ and his friends on an unforgettably thrilling adventure that uses groundbreaking technology. Loose articles are not permitted. Free lockers are available during a visit to this ride.

rides.FunFact: Reaches top speeds of 65 mph and towers 17 stories over Universal Studios Florida™.   Features six near-miss moments and first-ever thrills including a record-breaking loop.
rides.SocialSharingText: Don't miss out on details about Hollywood Rip Ride Rockit™ on the #UniversalOrlando moble app!
rides.MblShortDescription:
Adrenaline pumping and music thumping, you start climbing straight up. A moment later, you're screaming at 65 mph, 17 stories over Universal Studios Florida™. 

Loose articles are not permitted. Free lockers are available during a visit to this ride.

rides.FunFact: 1.5 million gallons of water are used in Jurassic Park River Adventure™.  When built, the ride's 85 foot plunge was the largest theme park water descent ever constructed.
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Jurassic Park River Adventure™ on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription: One minute, you’re gliding along in your raft. The next, you’re face to face with the giant T. rex. Your only escape is to take the pitch-black 85-foot plunge before you.

rides.FunFact:
There are 120 different alien species, many created specifically for this thrill ride. 

Each seat in every six-seat ride vehicle is equipped with a laser gun and gaming system that records each agent's score.
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out MEN IN BLACK™ Alien Attack™ on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription: New York has been hit by an epidemic of aliens and it's up to you, Agent Trainee, to blast them into oblivion. Loose articles are not permitted. Free lockers are available during a visit to this ride.

rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out One Fish, Two Fish, Red Fish, Blue Fish™ on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblDisplayName: One Fish, Two Fish, Red Fish, Blue Fish™
rides.MblShortDescription: Dr. Seuss' delightful book comes to life. Fly low and high, spinning and swooping. You'll pass an array of fountains that squirt in time to a musical rhyme.

rides.FunFact: Riders can get an extra soaking from park guests firing water cannons from the bow of Me Ship, the Olive.
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Popeye & Bluto's Bilge-Rat Barges® on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription: Hold on tight as you brave your way through raging rapids to rescue the best gal of Popeye®, Olive Oyl®. Get set for spectacular splashes and lots of silliness.

rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Pteranodon Flyers™ on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription:
Little adventurers can take flight beneath the wings of a Pteranodon, gently soaring through the air in a comfy seat suspended from a track above.

Note: Guests over 56” tall must be accompanied by a rider meeting the 36” height requirement.

rides.FunFact: Many of the Egyptian hieroglyphics on the walls spell out real words and ancient warnings.
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Revenge of the Mummy™ on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription: You'll plunge in total darkness, plagued by huge fireballs, swarms of scarab beetles and an army of warrior mummies on this one-of-a-kind roller coaster. Loose articles are not permitted. Free lockers are available during a visit to this ride.

rides.FunFact:
This attraction provides a bird's eye view of Seuss Landing on two separate tracks. 

The trolley travels through the Circus McGurkus Cafe Stoo-pendous™ restaurant!
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out The High in the Sky Seuss Trolley Train Ride!™ on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblDisplayName: The High in the Sky Seuss Trolley Train Ride!™
rides.MblShortDescription: Sit back and relax as you wind your way above the imaginative buildings and rides of Seuss Landing™ on one of two tracks featuring the Sneetches or the ABCs of your other favorite Seuss stories.

rides.FunFact: Shrek 4-D features an original 3-D film starring the vocal talents of the movies' original cast.
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Shrek 4-D on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription: With your OgreVision glasses (and a few special effects), you'll see, hear and feel the action of this all-new Shrek and Donkey adventure movie.

rides.FunFact: The ride has a total of seven inversions and two subterranean trenches during the 2-minute 15-second ride.
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out The Incredible Hulk Coaster® on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription:
Feel the rush of becoming a gamma-charged Hulk. As you race up to 67 miles per hour, your world turns upside down in zero gravity and this enhanced, high-speed roller coaster empowers you with the strength of a Super Hero.

Loose articles are not permitted. Free lockers are available during a visit to this ride.

rides.FunFact:
State-of-the-art digital projectors cover an 80 ft. diameter dome surface with an image four times the standard High Definition found in most home theaters, and twice what you'd experience in a normal digital theater. 

All the character voices in the attraction were performed by the original stars of the long-running The Simpsons show.
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out The Simpsons Ride™ on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription: Grab a seat with The Simpsons™ on a virtual reality roller coaster ride. You'll smash and blast through Krustyland with Homer, Marge, Bart, Lisa and Maggie in an over-the-top adventure.

rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out TRANSFORMERS: The Ride-3D on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription: Board your N*E*S*T* vehicle and join Optimus Prime and Bumblebee to help save mankind. You'll fight to keep the AllSpark out of Megatron's hands in an explosive battle between the Autobots and Decepticons.

rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Woody Woodpecker's Nuthouse Coaster™ on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription: Woody definitely proved he's got a few screws loose when he designed this kid-sized roller coaster that's fun for all ages! Perfect for first-timers.

rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Harry Potter and the Escape From Gringotts™ on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app
rides.MblDisplayName: Harry Potter and the Escape from Gringotts™
rides.MblShortDescription: Enter Gringotts™ bank and take a journey deep underground aboard this mind-blowing, multi-dimensional thrill ride. You’ll encounter Harry, Ron, and Hermione as you try to evade the wrath of Voldemort™ and Bellatrix to make it back to Diagon Alley™.

rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Hogwarts™ Express - Hogsmeade Station on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app
rides.MblShortDescription: Guests with a Park-to-Park admission ticket can enter Hogsmeade™ Station and catch the train to King's Cross Station. As you wind your way through British countryside to the outskirts of London, keep watch out your window; you never know who or what you might see. The last train departs at the earliest closing time of Universal Studios Florida™ or Universal's Islands of Adventure™, whichever park closes first.

rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Hogwarts™ Express - King's Cross Station on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app -
rides.MblShortDescription: Guests with a Park-to-Park admission ticket can enter King’s Cross Station and catch the train to Hogsmeade™ Station. On your journey, get ready to encounter familiar characters and creatures from the Harry Potter™ films. The last train departs at the earliest closing time of Universal Studios Florida™ or Universal’s Islands of Adventure™, whichever park closes first.

Brave the dangers of a mysterious island on a treacherous jungle expedition. As prehistoric predators attack from all sides, the most colossal ape ever to walk the Earth—King Kong—battles them off. Is he your hero or the ultimate foe?

rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Race Through New York Starring Jimmy Fallon™ on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app
rides.MblDisplayName: Race Through New York Starring Jimmy Fallon™
rides.MblShortDescription:
Take the show for a ride! Experience the history and fun of The Tonight Show in Studio 6B.  Send a "Thank You note" at the interactive desks, see Hashtag the Panda and enjoy a hip hop barber shop performance by the Ragtime Gals!
Then, join Jimmy Fallon and all your favorite characters from The Tonight Show in a fun-filled race through, below and above New York City.

Water is Life. Life is Joy. That's the philosophy celebrated at Universal's Volcano Bay™ water theme park. It's the carefree attitude the fabled Waturi islanders have embraced on their Pacific isle for centuries. Now you can live the Waturi way at this all-new park where thrills and relaxation flow in perfect harmony.With the power of the TapuTapu™ wearable, there’s no standing in long lines, carrying rafts around the park, nothing between you and a full day of fun. It’s an all-new kind of paradise, just steps away from everything Universal Orlando Resort™ has to offer. 

At Universal's Volcano Bay™ water theme park the water is delightfully warm during the cooler months - no doubt heated by lava deep below the Krakatau™ volcano.
Now’s the time to join Hagrid™ as you fly deep into the Forbidden Forest, beyond the grounds of Hogwarts™ castle, on a thrilling roller coaster ride to discover the rarest magical creatures.

rides.FunFact:
The saucers travel at speeds of up to 13 mph, which is nearly 1/51,585,895 the speed of light.

The thrust of each saucer is powerful enough to lift it into orbit a breathtaking 10 feet above the earth.
rides.SocialSharingText: Checking out Kang & Kodos' Twirl 'n' Hurl on the #UniversalOrlando mobile app - via @UniversalOrl
rides.MblShortDescription:
Kang & Kodos' Twirl 'n' Hurl operates Saturdays and Sundays. 

Attention Earth Humans! Fun-loving Evil Aliens Kang and Kodos from The Simpsons take you on an intergalactic spin designed to send your lunch into orbit.

rides.MblDisplayName: Universal’s Holiday Experience featuring Macy’s Balloons
rides.MblShortDescription: In this brand new walk-through experience at Universal Studios, you’ll get closer than ever to larger-than-life Macy’s balloons and colorful Christmas floats. There’s never been a better chance to get your photo with these beloved giant balloons. Santa Claus himself will be there to pose for photos as well.

Go inside the high-stakes world of Fast & Furious for a full-throttle, high-octane experience. You’ll meet up with the family, but just as the party is getting started an enemy from the past shows up and a wild chase ensues. It’s up to Dom, Letty, Hobbs and the rest of the crew to save the day in this action-packed new ride.
